text: The 2020 Nevada Senate election will be held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020. Voters in 10 districts of the Nevada Senate will elect their senators. The elections will coincide with the elections for other offices, including for U.S. President, U.S. House and the Nevada Assembly. Republicans need to gain three seats to win control of the chamber. The primary elections will be hold on June 9, 2020. == Background == In the 2018 Nevada Senate elections, Democrats maintained control of the Nevada Senate by a 13–8 margin.
